==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anelectrotonus
<hw>An`e*lec*trot"o*nus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ up + E. <ets>electrotonus</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The condition of decreased irritability of a
nerve in the region of the positive electrode or anode on the passage of
a current of electricity through it.</def> <rj><au>Foster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

